		"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">With a loud noise of your choosing and a sharp, potentially rude, gesture, you draw the attention of creatures within the targeted area toward you and away from others.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">On a failed save, creatures within the 10ft square gain disadvantage on Perception checks until the start of your next turn unless those Perception checks involve you. In addition, one creature of your choice can attempt to hide, even if they lack cover or concealment, from affected targets. If they intend to remain hidden after the end of your next turn, however, they must seek cover or concealment as normal.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">At levels 5, 10, and 15 you can choose additional creatures that may attempt to hide without cover or concealment.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
